message.content: First, we find $f(1+i)$. Since $1+i$ is not real, $f(1+i) = (1+i)^2 = 1 + 2i - 1 = \boxed{2i}$. Now, we find $f(f(f(f(1+i)))) = f(f(f(2i)))$. Since $2i$ is not real, $f(f(f(2i))) = f(f(-(2i)^2)) = f(f(-4))$. Now, $-4$ is real, so $f(f(-4)) = f(-4)^2$. Since $-4$ is real, $f(-4) = -(-4)^2 = -16$. Finally, $f(f(-4)) = f(-16)^2 = (-16)^2 = \boxed{256}$.
